-- Cencosud Sees 10-12 Paris Stores in Peru by 2015, Mercurio Says
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-06-16T16:35:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-16/cencosud-sees-10-12-paris-stores-in-peru-by-2015-mercurio-says.html
Chilean retailer  Cencosud SA (CENCOSUD)  plans
to open 10 to 12 of its Paris brand stores in Peru before the
end of 2015, Santiago-based newspaper El Mercurio said, citing
Jaime Soler, head of department-store operations.  The company will start moving into Peru in the first
quarter of 2013, Soler said, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
